Vintage-style illustration of an intricate mechanical contraption featuring brass gears, copper pipes, and Victorian-era machinery. At one end, a large ornate funnel collects streams of glowing orange data particles flowing from an antique filing cabinet with many small drawers. The particles travel through transparent glass tubes and spinning cogwheels, transforming as they move through the system. At the output end, the processed data emerges as perfectly organized golden streams feeding into an elegant crystal reservoir. The entire apparatus sits on a weathered wooden workbench with scattered engineering blueprints beneath. Warm sepia tones dominate with accents of amber and copper. Steam wisps curl around the machinery, giving it an active, working feel. The background shows a dimly lit workshop with brick walls and gas lamps casting soft pools of light.
